Date: March 5, 2026

Session Summary:
Began implementation of the rolling buffer architecture. This is a core component of the SoftScreen pipeline — the buffer holds a short window of frames to stabilize detections over time, eliminate flicker, maintain audio/video sync, and allow slightly forward-looking decisions before frames are released to output.

This architecture is central to what makes SoftScreen work as a real-time passthrough device rather than a simple frame-by-frame filter.

Progress:
- Rolling buffer structure initiated
- Early framework for frame windowing in place
- Foundation laid for stable sync between detection and output stream

Next:
- Continue buffer development and stress testing
- Integrate with live HDMI input pipeline
- Validate sync stability under real content conditions

Status: In progress — foundation complete, integration ahead
